Abuja (Sundiata Post) – A family of seven and the guest who was pregnant were discovered dead in their home this morning at Olowora Street, Mafoluku, Oshodi, Lagos. As the cause is yet to be determined, fear has gripped residents of in the area as there is apprehension at the Street as the man, his wife, their four children and a pregnant guest were all discovered lifeless around 10 am today. At the moment people are suspecting a likely food poisoning. Policemen at Makinde are said to have been notified and were at the residence to evacuate the bodies. (The Nation)